 a nation-state of equal citizens. Uncovering the false promise of liberalism, State of White Supremacy reveals race to be a fundamental, if flexible, ruling logic that perpetually generates and legitimates racial hierarchy and privilege. Racial domination and violence in the United States are indelibly marked by its origin and ongoing development as an empire-state. The widespread misrecognition of the United States as a liberal nation-state hinges on the twin conditions of its approximation for the white majority and its impossibility for their racial others. The essays in this book incisively probe and critique the U.S. racial state through a broad range of topics, including citizenship, education, empire, gender, genocide, geography, incarceration, Islamophobia, migration and border enforcement, violence, and welfare.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aMinoritieszUnited StatesxSocial conditions. 0aRacismzUnited StatesxHistory. 4ademocracy. 4aeducation policy. 4aeducation. 4afundamental organizing principle of American sociopolitical life. 4aimperialist expansion. 4amilitary actions. 4apolice racial boundaries. 4aprison-industrial-complex. 4aracism. 4asocial justice. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Discrimination & Race Relations.2bisacsh1 aBonilla-Silva, Eduardo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCosta Vargas, João H., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJung, Moon-Kie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477744540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804777445423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804777445.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d